    "Studies comparing the nutritional content of best-selling Chinese online set meals revealed that 89.56% contained less than 50 points out of 100, which means significant problems must be solved (Dai et al., 2022).",
    "Moreover, bulk consumption of these meals would also lead to a high intake of oil, salt, and sugar, contributing to weight gain and blood lipid profiles (Mehta et al., 2022).",
